# Spike build outputs — never committed (the spike's durable output is ADR 0005, not binaries).
**/bin/
**/obj/
**/pub/
**/dist/
**/node_modules/
**/*.vsix

# Story 23.1 Nuxt-over-IR spike (spike/nuxt-ir): Nuxt build state + the extracted proxy-IR bundle and the
# copied shipped stylesheet — all regenerable via `npm run ir && npm run generate`.
**/.nuxt/
**/.output/
**/ir-data/
nuxt-ir/public/specscribe.css

# NOTE (code review 2026-07-23): `package-lock.json` and `measurements/` were previously ignored. They are NOT
# ignored any more and MUST be committed — a spike whose deliverable is a set of numbers has to land the
# lockfile that pins the measured versions (the report cites `npm ci`, which cannot run without one) and the
# machine-written `measurements/measurements.json` those numbers came from. The originals were lost with the
# spike worktree; re-running `npm install && npm run ir && npm run generate && npm run measure` regenerates both.
